APPENDICES

A. Mathematical Derivations

A.1 Derivation of Metric from Fisher Information

For two nearby states $\rho$ and $\rho + \delta\rho$, the quantum Fisher information defines a metric on state space:

ds^2 = \frac{1}{2} \operatorname{Tr}[\delta\rho \mathcal{L}_\rho(\delta\rho)]
\tag{A.1}

where $\mathcal{L}_\rho$ is the symmetric logarithmic derivative. For Gaussian states, this reduces to correlation functions of field derivatives, leading to our $C_{\mu\nu}$ definition.

A.2 Regularization Scheme

To handle $\det C \to 0$, we use:

g_{\mu\nu} = \mathcal{N} [\det(C + \epsilon I)]^{-1/d} C_{\mu\nu}
\tag{A.2}

with $\epsilon \sim 1/N$ where $N$ is number of boundary degrees of freedom. This corresponds to a UV cutoff at entanglement scale.

